Familiarisation with and rehearsal of major ethnographic methods, collective analysis of fieldwork experiences.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to give an overview of major ethnographic methods (interview, participant observation, autoethnography) and to develop students' interviewing, listening and observation skills through hands-on assignments and reflections thereof. Guidelines for organizing materials are provided in order to facilitate their late use and analysis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students -	are familiar with basic ethnographic methods -	have practiced interviewing, listening to the interviewee, participant observation and autoethnographic observation.   -	analyse their fieldwork experience -	organize materials according to provided guidelines
